description: Rescuers raced to save people trapped in the rubble after the 7.4-magnitude quake killed at least nine people and injured more than 1,000 in Taiwan. It was the most powerful earthquake to strike Taiwan in a quarter century. NBC News' Janis Mackey Frayer reports.
title: Deadly earthquake in Taiwan traps dozens, causes widespread damage

description: Hundreds of U.S. nationals have been evacuated from Haiti since last month, escaping the ongoing violence, but many more are stuck there, desperately looking for ways to escape.
title: Desperation rises as Americans still in Haiti scramble to find ways to escape

description: The mayor of Medellín, the second-largest city in Colombia, announced a temporary ban on prostitution in two neighborhoods after an American tourist was discovered in a hotel room with two underage girls.
title: Medellín, Colombia, bans sex work in two areas after U.S. tourist found with minors

description: Just five minutes into a meeting with President Joe Biden, a Palestinian American doctor who has treated gravely injured patients in Gaza couldn’t bear to stay, so he left.
title: Displeasure with Biden's handling of Hamas-Israel war was on display at closed-door White House meeting

description: Haitians are fleeing Port-au-Prince mostly to escape unrelenting gang violence, according to a United Nations report released Tuesday.
title: Surge in violence forces more than 53,000 to flee Port-au-Prince in less than 3 weeks

description: Botswana is threatening to send 20,000 elephants to Germany in response to a possible ban on trophy hunting
title: Botswana threatens to send 20,000 elephants to Germany in protest of trophy hunting ban

description: In the Mexican state of Guanajuato mayoral candidate Gisela Gaytán was shot dead on the first day of her campaign despite having requested security protection from authorities and receiving no response.
title: In Mexico, a mayoral candidate is murdered on her first day of campaigning

description: Pope Francis led thousands of people in a moment of silence Wednesday to pray for the aid workers killed by an Israeli strike in Gaza and a young Ukrainian soldier named Oleksandre who was killed in ‘’this madness of war.”
title: Pope shows off rosary of slain Ukrainian soldier, denounces ‘madness of war’

description: Luis Rubiales, the disgraced former president of Spain’s soccer federation who kissed a player on the lips without her consent at the Women’s World Cup final, was arrested Wednesday as part of a separate corruption probe by Spanish police before being released.
title: Spanish police arrest ex-soccer federation head Rubiales on return to country amid corruption probe

description: A 7.4-magnitude earthquake struck Taiwan causing extensive damage throughout the country and the tsunami warnings in the region. NBC News’ Janis Mackey Frayer reports on the strongest quake to hit the island in at least 25 years.
title: Taiwan hit by strongest earthquake in at least 25 years

description: President Biden paid tribute to the World Central Kitchen aid workers killed in Gaza on Monday in a series of Israeli airstrikes, calling them "brave and selfless." All seven of them have now been identified. Israel, meanwhile, is facing growing fallout over the incident. NBC’s Raf Sanchez reports for TODAY.
title: Biden pays tribute to the 'brave' aid workers killed in Israeli airstrike

description: Taiwan has been hit by the strongest earthquake there in decades. The death toll is quickly rising with rescue efforts underway for families trapped in buildings. NBC’s Janis Mackey Frayer reports for TODAY.
title: Frantic rescue efforts underway after strong earthquake hits Taiwan

description: British counterterrorism police investigating the stabbing of a journalist who works for a TV channel critical of the Iranian government said that three suspects had fled the country within hours of the attack.
title: Suspects in the stabbing of an Iranian presenter fled U.K. after attack, counterterrorism police say

description: Uganda’s constitutional court on Wednesday upheld an anti-gay law that allows the death penalty for “aggravated homosexuality.”
title: Ugandan court rejects bid to nullify anti-gay law that provides for the death penalty in some cases

description: Eight passengers, including six Americans and two Australians, were stranded on a remote island off of the coast of Africa after they missed their ship's all aboard call time. All passengers eventually boarded the ship and will be reimbursed for their travel costs, according to the Norwegian Cruise Line.
title: Eight cruise passengers stranded on remote island after missing call time

description: Several buildings have collapsed in Hualien, Taiwan, after a 7.4 magnitude earthquake struck on the east coast of Taiwan around 8 a.m. local time.
title: Magnitude 7.4 earthquake rattles the coast of Taiwan
